SIMPLE: true
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: True
<hw>True</hw> <pr>(tr⟦udd⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Truer</adjf>
<pr>(tr⟦udd⟧"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Truest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>trewe</ets>, AS.
<ets>tre⟦oacute⟧we</ets> faithful, true, from <ets>tre⟦oacute⟧w</ets>
fidelity, faith, troth; akin to OFries. <ets>triuwe</ets>, adj.,
<ets>treuwa</ets>, n., OS. <ets>triuwi</ets>, adj., <ets>trewa</ets>,
n., D. <ets>trouw</ets>, adj. & n., G. <ets>treu</ets>, adj.,
<ets>treue</ets>, n., OHG. <ets>gitriuwi</ets>, adj., <ets>triuwa</ets>,
<pos>n.</pos>, Icel. <ets>tryggr</ets>, adj., Dan. <ets>tro</ets>, adj.
& n., Sw. <ets>trogen</ets>, adj., <ets>tro</ets>, n., Goth.
<ets>triggws</ets>, adj., <ets>triggwa</ets>, n., <ets>trauan</ets> to
trust, OPruss <ets>druwis</ets> faith. Cf. <er>Trow</er>,
<er>Trust</er>, <er>Truth</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Conformable to fact; in accordance with the actual
state of things; correct; not false, erroneous, inaccurate, or the like;
<as>as, a <ex>true</ex> relation or narration; a <ex>true</ex> history;
a declaration is <ex>true</ex> when it states the facts</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Right to precision; conformable to a rule or
pattern; exact; accurate; <as>as, a <ex>true</ex> copy; a <ex>true</ex>
likeness of the original</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Making his eye, foot, and hand keep <qex>true</qex> time.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Steady in adhering to friends, to promises, to a
prince, or the like; unwavering; faithful; loyal; not false, fickle, or
perfidious; <as>as, a <ex>true</ex> friend; a wife <ex>true</ex> to her
husband; an officer <ex>true</ex> to his charge</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy so <qex>true</qex>,⟦br⟧
So faithful, love unequaled.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dare to be <qex>true</qex>: nothing can need a lie.</q>
<rj><qau>Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Actual; not counterfeit, adulterated, or pretended;
genuine; pure; real; <as>as, <ex>true</ex> balsam; <ex>true</ex> love of
country; a <ex>true</ex> Christian</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>true</qex> light which lighteth every man that cometh
into the world.</q> <rj><qau>John i. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>True</qex> ease in writing comes from art, not chance.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Genuine; real; not deviating from
the essential characters of a class; <as>as, a lizard is a <ex>true</ex>
reptile; a whale is a <ex>true</ex>, but not a <xex>typical</xex>,
mammal</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>True</xex> is sometimes used elliptically for
<xex>It is true</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Out of true</b></col>, <cd>varying from correct
mechanical form, alignment, adjustment, etc.; -- said of a wall that is
not perpendicular, of a wheel whose circumference is not in the same
plane, and the like.</cd> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> -- <col><b>A true
bill</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a bill of indictment which is
returned by the grand jury so indorsed, signifying that the charges to
be true.</cd> -- <col><b>True time</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Time</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>True</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: True
<hw>True</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In accordance with truth;
truly.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>True-blue</ent>⟦br⟧
